➜双语漫画 | 我们闪光的那一瞬间，是遇见独立的自己
http://www.sohu.com/a/433646957_115013	1800
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p1.itc.cn/images01/20201123/ac8bcf61f21b4479be0ef3ea62fa7bf3.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>31-year-old Lainey Molnar is on a mission to empower women, and she's using her creative expression to do so. Molnar creates honest comics that cut through all of the filters and focus on women's role in society and the way it perceives them.</p>
<p>31岁的莱尼·莫尔纳着力于用她富有创造性的表达方式赋予女性力量。莫尔纳创作了一系列十分真实的漫画，抛掉形色各样的滤镜，聚焦于女性在社会中的角色以及社会看待她们的方式。</p>
<p>"I started my career as my country's first personal blogger. After my blogging days, I stepped away from the limelight because of the habitual online harassment I received, so when [the place I live in] went into lockdown [due to the pandemic] earlier this year, I decided to create a comic-style avatar for myself and started posting drawings about her to process what I'm going through (or all of us go through) as a woman under the pressure of society and just simply... life."</p>
<p>我的职业生涯开始于我的国家的第一个个人博客。博客之后，我离开了众人关注的中心，因为我受到网上习惯性的骚扰，所以今年早些时候(疫情开始封城的时候)，我决定为自己创建一个漫画风格的头像，并开始发布这些内容，以处理我(或者我们所有)作为一个女人在社会的压力下，只是简单地...生活的经历。</p>
<p>我妈妈31岁 vs 我31岁</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p7.itc.cn/images01/20201123/0012bc9ccf9143e7954a46177ed4ea88.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>            <div class="lookall-box">
